&lt;p&gt;The Data Team is on a mission to represent medical reality by transforming raw data into products that directly generate value for customers and help bring cutting-edge medical technology to the patients who need it most. We thrive on the challenge of turning complex healthcare data into simple, trusted, and actionable insights while continuously improving the quality and intelligence of our platform.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of this team, you&#39;ll build deep expertise in our data assets while partnering closely with engineers and product teams to strengthen the accuracy, reliability, and customer impact of everything we deliver.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Customer Data Investigation&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Investigate customer questions about data displayed throughout the AcuityMD platform using SQL.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Research issues end-to-end, identify root causes, and validate findings across multiple data sources.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Distinguish between expected platform behavior, customer education opportunities, and true product defects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate findings clearly to Customer Success, Support, and customers when appropriate.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create detailed engineering tickets with reproduction steps, supporting evidence, and root-cause analysis.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Platform &amp;amp; Product Improvement&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build deep expertise in AcuityMD&#39;s data model, business logic, and data pipelines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with Engineering, Product, Customer Success, and Support to improve platform quality and customer trust.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify recurring issues and opportunities to improve data quality, tooling, and operational processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help Engineering validate fixes and ensure customer issues are fully resolved.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
