&lt;p&gt;Working within the Product organization, this person will partner closely with Engineering to define, write, and continuously improve the data context and evaluation framework that becomes a strategic differentiator for AcuityMD&#39;s AI products. At the same time, they&#39;ll serve as the internal authority on healthcare data, enabling Sales, Customer Success, and Product to confidently explain what our data means - and just as importantly, what it doesn&#39;t.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Team Mission&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The AcuityMD platform features data from across the healthcare industry. Our data assets are the foundation of our application and central to the value we deliver to clients. Every data asset requires context to know how to interpret it, its nuances, and limitations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support our commercial teams so our customers are successful by answering the toughest data questions internally around what datasets mean, and the nuanced limitations of how to use them.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate closely with our engineering team to build our AI data context layer with evals. This requires deep understanding of the data and great technical writing skills. This role should help drive what our eval designs even are to measure agent quality.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help drive what tooling we need to build in our data products to support data explainability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
